words: My parents had decided that we had to move to, out of
the house we were living in in New York um right when I
was going to go to college; the year, the summer right
before I was a freshman in college. So um
that was kind of tough especially like at that time where you know you're going to miss, you
know you're going to miss your friends and all of those people that you had in high school. Even though you know
it's going to change it kind of just was hard to
move. Especially because we were moving way out of state. We were moving to North Carolina which
is again like a ten hour drive from where I live on Long Island, where
I lived on Long Island to North Carolina. But although this was
kind of um a far drive and
far trip to take especially you know going to college
and I picked the college because I thought I was going to be relatively close to home and then it came,
turned out I wasn't as close to home as I thought I was going to be. Um
it was hard to you know let go of the house that I lived in as
a child, even like at twenty. Well I was eighteen or nineteen
at the time, now I'm twenty but at that age you know I'm kind of growing into my
own person and becoming independent and you know I don't have that
home to fall back on anymore because North Carolina is not very familiar to me
even though its the address I put down as my permanent address. It
is not as comfortable to me of an
area as New York was or even as Philadelphia is. But
although it's made an impact on me it's made a bigger one on my siblings.
Um they're both younger than me. One of them is in, going into seventh grade and one
of them is going into um eleventh grade. So they were kind of ripped out of
their life in New York almost. You know they had everything set. They had their friends.
They knew their school district. And it's much different than
it is, than it was in New York. You know the schools are different, the life is different, the
area, everything is different. So I really feel for them more than
I feel for myself because this whole thing has really allowed me to you know become
independent and be comfortable moving to different places whether it be coming here
this summer or it be um you know just
moving around going to conferences and stuff for my research.
So I hope that it turns out to be good for them too
because they do seem to have a brighter future ahead of them with the state schools
